text:
Social Conditions in Manhattan: Shown is the sink which provides all the water for the families at No. 260½ Water Street. It is barely big enough to permit a man to wash. The community toilet is on the other side of a thin partition at the right. Published in the New York Evening World of February 23, 1926.

February 23, 1926.

Gift of New York World.
title: Social conditions in Manhattan.
